<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 5:57PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Heavy snow showers will impact portions of Fergus County
through 650 PM MDT...
At 550 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking heavy snow showers near
Lewistown, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Visibility less than a half mile due to heavy snow.
SOURCE...Observed.
IMPACT...Highly variable road conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Moore, Giltedge, Glengarry, Heath and Forestgrove.</description>
<instruction>Use extreme caution if traveling in this area.</instruction>
